<section id="browser-support">
  <h2>Browser Support</h2>
  <p>The CSS <code>shape()</code> function is supported in all major browsers.</p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Feature</th>
        <th>Chrome</th>
        <th>Firefox</th>
        <th>Safari</th>
        <th>Edge</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>clip-path: shape()</code></td>
        <td>135+</td>
        <td>148+</td>
        <td>18.4+</td>
        <td>135+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>calc()</code> inside shape()</td>
        <td>135+</td>
        <td>148+</td>
        <td>18.4+</td>
        <td>135+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Custom properties in shape()</td>
        <td>135+</td>
        <td>148+</td>
        <td>18.4+</td>
        <td>135+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shape animation interpolation</td>
        <td>135+</td>
        <td>148+</td>
        <td>18.4+</td>
        <td>135+</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>Older browsers see plain rectangles. The <code>@supports</code> guard prevents any broken rendering.</p>
</section>
